<subSubSection id="E1BA6E130D4ABC9C95F15FED96E9999D" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="06C8FE6F500296C6EA523195DBD82084" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D0FB858568DCFC8444E66DE6098B496" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">
<taxonomicName id="195EDA4BD5BC8C7496C1678673249EB0" authorityName="Y. H. Tan &amp; H. B. Ding" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Petrocosmea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Petrocosmea rhombifolia" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhombifolia">
<emphasis id="5CBAE9BDF5F2B874496C43186D2F72BF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">Petrocosmea rhombifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="CE167C353F5603D7D6491AF37D9527C9" genus="P." lsidName="P. rosettifolia" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" rank="species" species="rosettifolia">
<emphasis id="2BA56A73BD3D9C0A72771952F9203D40" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">P. rosettifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from the latter in having rhombic leaf blades (vs. broadly ovate to orbicular or broadly elliptic) and much longer petiole to 15 cm long (vs. to 4 cm long); the flowers have upper white lip (vs. purple-blue flowers throughout), corolla adaxial lip 14-15 
<normalizedToken id="EBB96E51B138A3510A0EFCB77AD0C025" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
9-10 mm (vs. ca. 5 mm), abaxial lip 27-28 
<normalizedToken id="EF1B6D1C7B2DAE8BB0ACFD124528FA7B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
12-14 mm (vs. ca. 7-8 
<normalizedToken id="31D80B0F0F2849F122B973B243EC16B9" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6-8 mm), and flowering March-April (vs. October).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
